Generate a fully self-contained HTML performance report from the uploaded LoadRunner Excel file with the following features:
Sticky Top Navigation Header
Links to: Consolidated Table, Consolidated Bar Chart, all release sections detected dynamically from sheets matching the pattern Release M*, and Observations & Recommendations.
Header remains visible while scrolling. Clicking links scrolls smoothly to the corresponding section.
Consolidated Section (Homepage)
Render the full consolidated sheet. First 3 rows as table headers.
Add a filterable bar chart below the table:
X-axis names shortened for laptop view
Y-axis: response time
Bars colored: Green ≤3s, Red >3s
Param Sheet Mapping
Use the Param sheet to enrich transactions.
Main calls: display Transaction Name, URL empty.
Sub-transactions: display Sub-Transaction Name, URL from Param sheet.
Trim and normalize strings before joining.
Per-Release SLA Compliance Tables
Detect all releases dynamically (Release M* - Response Time).
Group: Functionality → Transaction → Sub-Transaction (Functionality used only for grouping).
Columns: Transaction / Sub-Transaction, URL, Min, Max, Avg, 90th Percentile, SLA Status.
SLA ≤3s = Under SLA (green), >3s = Breached (red).
Table features: Expand/collapse all, global search, per-column filter, hide unnecessary columns.
Top 5 Slowest Transactions & 90th Percentile Bar Chart
Derived per release from 90th percentile response times.
Sorted descending, hover tooltips, smooth animations.
X-axis names shortened for laptop view.
Release M – Graph Sheet Content*
Include all text, tables, charts, and images exactly as in Excel.
Place immediately after each release’s charts and tables.
Observations & Recommendations
Highlight SLA breaches (>3s) and slow transactions.
Provide client-friendly recommendations.
Layout and Styling
Full-width, no side padding.
Light theme with soft blue, green, and red accents.
Card-based sections with subtle shadows.
Tables: sticky headers, zebra stripes, row hover highlight.
Responsive design for laptop and larger screens.
Constraints
No backend or Python scripting.
No HTML upload controls.
No hardcoded release names.
SLA fixed at 3 seconds.
All values must come directly from Excel or derived dynamically.
Output Requirement
Generate a complete HTML page, including all CSS and JavaScript, fully interactive tables and charts, ready to save as a single .html file.
Sticky top navigation must automatically list all detected releases based on Release M* sheets.